<subSubSection id="A7CC2DBDFFD0FFFAFF6BFA2BFC2FFDA3" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="286" pageId="10" pageNumber="285" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="EF697E36FFD0FFFAFF6BFA2BFC2FFDA3" blockId="10.[151,1127,1485,1604]" lastBlockId="11.[113,1089,220,563]" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="286" pageId="10" pageNumber="285">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFD0FFFBFF6BFA2BFEB8FA54" bold="true" box="[151,262,1485,1508]" pageId="10" pageNumber="285">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFD0FFFBFEF1FA2BFE7EFA54" author="BOHEMAN" box="[269,448,1485,1508]" firstAuthor="BOHEMAN" pageId="10" pageNumber="285" refId="ref47955" refString="BOHEMAN C. H. 1855: Monographia Cassididarum. Tomus Tertius. Officina Norstedtiana, Holmiae, 543 pp. + 1 pl." type="book" year="1855">BOHEMAN (1855)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFD0FFFBFDCAFA2BFCF5FA54" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1855" box="[566,843,1485,1508]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Coptocycla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="285" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubrotestacea">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFD0FFFBFDCAFA2BFCF5FA54" box="[566,843,1485,1508]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="285">Coptocycla rubrotestacea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
presumably from a single specimen. Subsequently, the species was listed only in catalogues (see BOROWEC 1999a) and 
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFD0FFFBFF6BF9EBFEF0F994" author="BOROWIEC" box="[151,334,1549,1572]" firstAuthor="BOROWIEC" pageId="10" pageNumber="285" pagination="203 - 222" refId="ref48049" refString="BOROWIEC L. 1989: Three new species of Charidotella Weise (Coleoptera, Chrysomelidae, Cassidinae), with checklist of the genus. Polskie Pismo Entomologiczne 59: 203 - 222." type="journal article" year="1989">BOROWIEC (1989)</bibRefCitation>
synonymized it with 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFD0FFFBFDC8F9EBFC4BF994" authority="(Boheman, 1855)" baseAuthorityName="Boheman" baseAuthorityYear="1855" box="[564,1013,1549,1572]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Charidotella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="285" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ventricosa">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFD0FFFBFDC8F9EBFC8FF994" box="[564,817,1549,1572]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="285">Charidotella ventricosa</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFD0FFFBFCC3F9EBFC53F994" author="Boheman" box="[831,1005,1549,1572]" firstAuthor="Boheman" pageId="10" pageNumber="285" refId="ref47955" refString="BOHEMAN C. H. 1855: Monographia Cassididarum. Tomus Tertius. Officina Norstedtiana, Holmiae, 543 pp. + 1 pl." type="book" year="1855">Boheman, 1855</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. However, 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFD0FFFBFF6BF9CBFEF2F9F4" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1855" box="[151,332,1581,1604]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Coptocycla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="285" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubrotestacea">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFD0FFFBFF6BF9CBFEF2F9F4" box="[151,332,1581,1604]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="285">C. rubrotestacea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs by the uniformly pale explanate margin of elytra (humeral spots always present in 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFD1FFFAFEC4FF3AFE76FF43" baseAuthorityName="Boheman" baseAuthorityYear="1855" box="[312,456,220,243]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Charidotella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="286" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ventricosa">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFD1FFFAFEC4FF3AFE76FF43" box="[312,456,220,243]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="286">C. ventricosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), subcircular body shape (subtriangular in 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFD1FFFAFC5DFF3AFB8FFF43" baseAuthorityName="Boheman" baseAuthorityYear="1855" box="[929,1073,220,243]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Charidotella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="286" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ventricosa">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFD1FFFAFC5DFF3AFB8FFF43" box="[929,1073,220,243]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="286">C. ventricosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), clypeus with an apical sulcus (smooth in 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFD1FFFAFDCCFF1AFD01FEA3" baseAuthorityName="Boheman" baseAuthorityYear="1855" box="[560,703,252,275]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Charidotella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="286" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ventricosa">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFD1FFFAFDCCFF1AFD01FEA3" box="[560,703,252,275]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="286">C. ventricosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and less convex elytra with much lower and obtuse postscutellar tubercle (high and sharp in 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFD1FFFAFD22FEFAFCD2FE83" baseAuthorityName="Boheman" baseAuthorityYear="1855" box="[734,876,284,307]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Charidotella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="286" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ventricosa">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFD1FFFAFD22FEFAFCD2FE83" box="[734,876,284,307]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="286">C. ventricosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). I therefore restore the species status of 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFD1FFFAFEB7FEDAFE42FEE3" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1855" box="[331,508,316,339]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Coptocycla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="286" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubrotestacea">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFD1FFFAFEB7FEDAFE42FEE3" box="[331,508,316,339]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="286">C. rubrotestacea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The quite unusual combination of morphological features of this species is similar only to 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFD1FFFAFE01FEBAFC34FEC3" authority="(Fabricius, 1801)" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1801" box="[509,906,348,371]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Charidotella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="286" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="morio">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFD1FFFAFE01FEBAFD75FEC3" box="[509,715,348,371]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="286">Charidotella morio</emphasis>
(Fabricius, 1801)
</taxonomicName>
, which differs by the primarily black ventral side (uniformly yellow in 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFD1FFFAFD5AFE9AFCE9FE23" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1855" box="[678,855,380,403]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Coptocycla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="286" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubrotestacea">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFD1FFFAFD5AFE9AFCE9FE23" box="[678,855,380,403]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="286">C. rubrotestacea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), explanate margin of elytra declivous in their entire length (canaliculate in apical third in 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFD1FFFAFCBEFE7AFC4AFE03" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1855" box="[834,1012,412,435]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Coptocycla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="286" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubrotestacea">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFD1FFFAFCBEFE7AFC4AFE03" box="[834,1012,412,435]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="286">C. rubrotestacea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), more constricted pronotum in its basal half, thus appearing subpentagonal (broadly rounded and nearly semicircular in 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFD1FFFAFEA1FE3AFDB0FE43" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1855" box="[349,526,476,499]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Coptocycla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="286" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubrotestacea">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFD1FFFAFEA1FE3AFDB0FE43" box="[349,526,476,499]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="286">C. rubrotestacea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and large basal teeth of claws (small in 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFD1FFFAFC3CFE3AFF15FDA3" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1855" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Coptocycla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="286" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubrotestacea">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFD1FFFAFC3CFE3AFF15FDA3" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="286">C. rubrotestacea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFD1FFFAFF3DFE1AFE5DFDA3" baseAuthorityName="Boheman" baseAuthorityYear="1855" box="[193,483,508,531]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Charidotella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="286" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubrotestacea">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFD1FFFAFF3DFE1AFE5DFDA3" box="[193,483,508,531]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="286">Charidotella rubrotestacea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is so far known only from the 
<typeStatus id="306DC094FFD1FFFAFCD0FE1AFC33FDA3" box="[812,909,508,531]" pageId="11" pageNumber="286">holotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
